{{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{flagicon|Slovenia}} "Dan najlepših sanj" | image = | caption = | year = 1996 | country = Slovenia | artist = Regina | as = | with = | language = Slovene | languages = | composer = [[Aleksander Kogoj]] | lyricist = [[Aleksander Kogoj]] | conductor = [[Jože Privšek]] | place = 21st | points = 19 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?1996si from Diggiloo Thrush] | prev = Prisluhni mi | prev_link = Prisluhni mi | next = Zbudi se | next_link = Zbudi se }} '''"Dan najlepših sanj"''' ("The day of the most beautiful dream") was the [[Slovenia in the Eurovision Song Contest 1996|Slovene]] entry in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1996]], sung by [[Regina (singer)|Regina]] in [[Slovene language|Slovenian]].
The song was performed fourteenth on the night, following [[France]]'s [[Dan Ar Braz|Dan Ar Braz & L'Héritage des Celtes]] with "[[Diwanit Bugale]]" and preceding [[Netherlands]]'s [[Maxine (singer)|Maxine]] & [[Franklin Brown]] with "[[De eerste keer]]". At the close of voting, it had received 19 points, placing twenty-first in a field of twenty three.
It was succeeded as Slovene representative at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1997|1997 contest]] by [[Tanja Ribič]] with "[[Zbudi se]]".
