{{Infobox bridge |bridge_name= Davtashen Bridge |image=Դավթաշենի կամուրջը.JPG |caption=Davtashen Bridge |official_name= |carries= |crosses=[[Hrazdan River]] |locale=[[Yerevan]] |maint= |id= |design= |mainspan= |length= {{convert|496|m|ft|1|abbr=on}} |width= {{convert|32|m|ft|1|abbr=on}} |height= {{convert|92|m|ft|1|abbr=on}} |clearance= |below= |traffic= Dual carriageway |open= 2000 |life= |closed= |map_cue= |map_image= |map_text= |map_width= |coordinates= {{Coord|40|12|36|N|44|29|34|E|}} |lat= |long= }}
'''Davtashen Bridge''' or '''Davitashen Bridge''' ({{lang-hy|Դավթաշենի կամուրջ}}) is a bridge for traffic linking across the [[Hrazdan River]] in [[Yerevan]], [[Armenia]]. It connects the Vaghrshyan street of [[Arabkir district]] with the Sasna Tzrer street of [[Davtashen district]] within the capital city. The construction process was launched during the 1970s by the Soviet government but abandoned shortly after. Only in 2000, the construction of the bridge was completed.<ref>[http://www.encyclopedia.am/pages.php?bId=1&hId=333 Bridges in Armenia]</ref> Height above the water level of the river Hrazdan -92m.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kamurjshin.am/en/showprogram/10/|title=KamurjShin.am|website=www.kamurjshin.am|language=en|access-date=2017-01-26}}</ref> The bridge was constructed by [[Kamurjshin]] company.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hhpress.am/index.php?sub=hodv&hodv=20110618_18&flag=am|title=HHpress.am|website=www.hhpress.am|access-date=2016-11-11}}</ref>
The bridge was designed by architect [[Rafael Israelyan]].<ref>[http://www.yerevan.am/edfiles/files/ANDZNAGIR/kamurjner+.pdf Bridges in Yerevan]</ref>
