{{Infobox language family |name=Lebonya |region=[[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone D|Zone D]]) |child1=[[Lengola language|Lengola]] |child2=[[Bodo language (Bantu)|Bodo]] |child3=[[Nyali languages|Nyali]] |glotto=lebo1246 |glottorefname=Lebonya }}
'''Lebonya''' is a proposed intermediate group of [[Bantu languages]] coded Zone D in Guthrie's classification. There are three branches: *[[Lengola language|Lengola]] *[[Bodo language (Bantu)|Bodo]] *the [[Nyali languages]]
''Glottolog'' 2.3 classifies Bodo instead as one of the [[Ngendan languages]].
